{
  "stem": "4122.2",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The first thing, I can't understand how yesterday's friends could be today's enemies.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "When, when they came in, the Germans, and they were taking us to all kind of work.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And then the-- then came the holidays.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "On, on all those kinds of works, we were taken-- they take us to paint houses.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I was never on a ladder until this-- on a step ladder-- until they took me to paint a building, a house, and all the other people-- old people, and [? this. ?] Until we were continued, so working, living at home, until the Yom Kippur [? war ?] came-- Yom Kippur came, and we were all in shul.",
      "word_count": 59
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "In 1941.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yeah.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And we hear that [? there were-- ?] there was an aksia in Podhajce.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "That they were taking people to kill.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "An aksia is when they take people and they just kill them.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They tell them they are, they're going to take them somewhere else, and they take and kill them.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So at this time we saw-- the gentiles came over and said that they were coming.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They-- in Podhajce is an aksia.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So we all fled from the schul to the fields to hide, because in our, in our city, in Zawalow, was a small congregation, but from around the villages they used to come, and it was a lot of people then in the shul.",
      "word_count": 44
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And we went in hiding via-- until the next day of Yom Kippur.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "After Yom Kippur, I recall that we came home from the hiding to our houses in the late in the afternoon.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And we continued the life normally until we hear that we will have-- they are bringing from all the villages to our city, all the Jews.",
      "word_count": 26
    }
  ],
